    "code": "02", 
    "data": "بِسْمِ ٱللَّهِ ٱلرَّحْمَٰنِ ٱلرَّحِيمِ\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nوَٱلنَّٰزِعَٰتِ غَرْقًا (1)\nI swear by the angels who violently pull out the souls of the wicked,\nوَٱلنَّٰشِطَٰتِ نَشْطًا (2)\nAnd by those who gently draw out the souls of the blessed,\nوَٱلسَّٰبِحَٰتِ سَبْحًا (3)\nAnd by those who float in space,\nفَٱلسَّٰبِقَٰتِ سَبْقًا (4)\nThen those who are foremost going ahead,\nفَٱلْمُدَبِّرَٰتِ أَمْرًا (5)\nThen those who regulate the affair.\nيَوْمَ تَرْجُفُ ٱلرَّاجِفَةُ (6)\nThe day on which the quaking one shall quake,\nتَتْبَعُهَا ٱلرَّادِفَةُ (7)\nWhat must happen afterwards shall follow it.\nقُلُوبٌ يَوْمَئِذٍ وَاجِفَةٌ (8)\nHearts on that day shall palpitate,\nأَبْصَٰرُهَا خَٰشِعَةٌ (9)\nTheir eyes cast down.\nيَقُولُونَ أَءِنَّا لَمَرْدُودُونَ فِى ٱلْحَافِرَةِ (10)\nThey say: Shall we indeed be restored to (our) first state?\nأَءِذَا كُنَّا عِظَٰمًا نَّخِرَةً (11)\nWhat! when we are rotten bones?\nقَالُوا۟ تِلْكَ إِذًا كَرَّةٌ خَاسِرَةٌ (12)\nThey said: That then would be a return occasioning loss.\nفَإِنَّمَا هِىَ زَجْرَةٌ وَٰحِدَةٌ (13)\nBut it shall be only a single cry,\nفَإِذَا هُم بِٱلسَّاهِرَةِ (14)\nWhen lo! they shall be wakeful.\nهَلْ أَتَىٰكَ حَدِيثُ مُوسَىٰٓ (15)\nHas not there come to you the story of Musa?\nإِذْ نَادَىٰهُ رَبُّهُۥ بِٱلْوَادِ ٱلْمُقَدَّسِ طُوًى (16)\nWhen his Lord called upon him in the holy valley, twice,\nٱذْهَبْ إِلَىٰ فِرْعَوْنَ إِنَّهُۥ طَغَىٰ (17)\nGo to Firon, surely he has become inordinate.\nفَقُلْ هَل لَّكَ إِلَىٰٓ أَن تَزَكَّىٰ (18)\nThen say: Have you (a desire) to purify yourself:\nوَأَهْدِيَكَ إِلَىٰ رَبِّكَ فَتَخْشَىٰ (19)\nAnd I will guide you to your Lord so that you should fear.\nفَأَرَىٰهُ ٱلْءَايَةَ ٱلْكُبْرَىٰ (20)\nSo he showed him the mighty sign.\nفَكَذَّبَ وَعَصَىٰ (21)\nBut he rejected (the truth) and disobeyed.\nثُمَّ أَدْبَرَ يَسْعَىٰ (22)\nThen he went back hastily.\nفَحَشَرَ فَنَادَىٰ (23)\nThen he gathered (men) and called out.\nفَقَالَ أَنَا۠ رَبُّكُمُ ٱلْأَعْلَىٰ (24)\nThen he said: I am your lord, the most high.\nفَأَخَذَهُ ٱللَّهُ نَكَالَ ٱلْءَاخِرَةِ وَٱلْأُولَىٰٓ (25)\nSo Allah seized him with the punishment of the hereafter and the former life.\nإِنَّ فِى ذَٰلِكَ لَعِبْرَةً لِّمَن يَخْشَىٰٓ (26)\nMost surely there is in this a lesson to him who fears.\nءَأَنتُمْ أَشَدُّ خَلْقًا أَمِ ٱلسَّمَآءُ بَنَىٰهَا (27)\nAre you the harder to create or the heaven? He made it.\nرَفَعَ سَمْكَهَا فَسَوَّىٰهَا (28)\nHe raised high its height, then put it into a right good state.\nوَأَغْطَشَ لَيْلَهَا وَأَخْرَجَ ضُحَىٰهَا (29)\nAnd He made dark its night and brought out its light.\nوَٱلْأَرْضَ بَعْدَ ذَٰلِكَ دَحَىٰهَآ (30)\nAnd the earth, He expanded it after that.\nأَخْرَجَ مِنْهَا مَآءَهَا وَمَرْعَىٰهَا (31)\nHe brought forth from it its water and its pasturage.\nوَٱلْجِبَالَ أَرْسَىٰهَا (32)\nAnd the mountains, He made them firm,\nمَتَٰعًا لَّكُمْ وَلِأَنْعَٰمِكُمْ (33)\nA provision for you and for your cattle.\nفَإِذَا جَآءَتِ ٱلطَّآمَّةُ ٱلْكُبْرَىٰ (34)\nBut when the great predominating calamity comes;\nيَوْمَ يَتَذَكَّرُ ٱلْإِنسَٰنُ مَا سَعَىٰ (35)\nThe day on which man shall recollect what he strove after,\nوَبُرِّزَتِ ٱلْجَحِيمُ لِمَن يَرَىٰ (36)\nAnd the hell shall be made manifest to him who sees\nفَأَمَّا مَن طَغَىٰ (37)\nThen as for him who is inordinate,\nوَءَاثَرَ ٱلْحَيَوٰةَ ٱلدُّنْيَا (38)\nAnd prefers the life of this world,\nفَإِنَّ ٱلْجَحِيمَ هِىَ ٱلْمَأْوَىٰ (39)\nThen surely the hell, that is the abode.\nوَأَمَّا مَنْ خَافَ مَقَامَ رَبِّهِۦ وَنَهَى ٱلنَّفْسَ عَنِ ٱلْهَوَىٰ (40)\nAnd as for him who fears to stand in the presence of his Lord and forbids the soul from low desires,\nفَإِنَّ ٱلْجَنَّةَ هِىَ ٱلْمَأْوَىٰ (41)\nThen surely the garden-- that is the abode.\nيَسْـَٔلُونَكَ عَنِ ٱلسَّاعَةِ أَيَّانَ مُرْسَىٰهَا (42)\nThey ask you about the hour, when it will come.\nفِيمَ أَنتَ مِن ذِكْرَىٰهَآ (43)\nAbout what! You are one to remind of it.\nإِلَىٰ رَبِّكَ مُنتَهَىٰهَآ (44)\nTo your Lord is the goal of it.\nإِنَّمَآ أَنتَ مُنذِرُ مَن يَخْشَىٰهَا (45)\nYou are only a warner to him who would fear it.\nكَأَنَّهُمْ يَوْمَ يَرَوْنَهَا لَمْ يَلْبَثُوٓا۟ إِلَّا عَشِيَّةً أَوْ ضُحَىٰهَا (46)\nOn the day that they see it, it will be as though they had not tarried but the latter part of a day or the early part of it.", 
    "title": "79: An-Naazi'aat النازعات"
}